reviewText:
As someone who isn't a fan of the top down mobas (dota,LOL.ext) this game doesn't seem like it adds much on the surface, just a change in controls to w,a,s,d and a third person view. but this makes this moba more about hitting basics and Abilities leading shots with the mouse allowing a level of skill that simply isn't in a game like dota .This is not to say games like this don't take skill, they clearly do it's just that smite has a direnet type of skill needed.

The combat is much more based on a adrenalin filled action packed spam of abilities than the well calculated moves in a typical moba but that doesn't change that a player with a strategy will most likely win a skirmish against a player that doesn't. Abilities are much more satisfying as all of the gods in the game only have 1 passive and the abilities bound to the first  4 number keys are cast making the player feel like they have an actual effect raver that giving him a simple buff that an item could give him/her;

The item system is much simpler than the other mobas that really lends to the game, you could call this game a gateway into more typical mobas" but i have played this game as soon it came out of beta and  those games still don't appeal to me
